sql:
SELECT quarter_name
FROM financial_quarters
WHERE year = 2023;

SELECT quarter_name
FROM financial_quarters
ORDER BY start_date ASC;

SELECT quarter_name
FROM financial_quarters
ORDER BY quarter_name;

SELECT metric_id
FROM forecasts
WHERE forecasted_value > 100;

SELECT year, date(AVG(julianday(start_date))) AS average_start_date
FROM financial_quarters
GROUP BY year;

SELECT metric_name
FROM financial_metrics
WHERE metric_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'total spending' refers to the financial metric 'All Expenditure';
- 'initial quarter of 2023' corresponds to 'Q1 2023';
- 'user with ID 1' indicates the specific user whose permissions are being queried.

sql:
SELECT metric_name, COUNT(*) AS total_count
FROM financial_metrics
GROUP BY metric_name;

external_knowledge:
Significant financial impact refers to the total value of financial metrics for each quarter; stacking up against each other implies a comparison of these values to identify the quarters performing better financially.;
The query focuses on quarters from the most impactful down to the least impactful based on the summed financial metric values.;
Financial quarters are periods used in financial reporting, typically representing three-month segments of a fiscal year.;
